  "strengths": "Explicitly enforces synthetic-only constraints and clear safety boundaries. The 'stop gate' concept effectively isolates ethical considerations from technical analysis, preventing premature conclusions.",
  "risks": "Over-reliance on automated gates might obscure nuanced human factors. If 'preliminary_internal_non_final' status is ignored, users might treat outputs as definitive. Lack of real-world context could reduce training efficacy for complex ethical dilemmas.",
  "improvement": "Integrate dynamic scenario variations to test gate robustness. Add explicit feedback loops for ethical decision-making rather than binary stops. Ensure documentation clearly distinguishes between simulation artifacts and potential real-world implications, reinforcing the 'no final claims' rule."
